  <description>Welcome to the Splunk Innovators Toolkit - Your Guide to Building Interactive Dashboards</description>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 30px; text-align: center;">
          <h1 style="font-size: 36px; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #FD1875;">Welcome to the Splunk Innovators Toolkit</h1>
          <p style="font-size: 18px; color: #A0A0A0; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 30px;">
            Production-ready UI components that make building interactive Splunk dashboards easy and fun.
            Whether you're a beginner or an experienced developer, this toolkit has everything you need.
          </p>
          <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
            <a href="demo" class="sit-btn sit-btn-primary sit-btn-lg" style="text-decoration: none;">View Live Demo</a>
            <a href="component_reference" class="sit-btn sit-btn-outline sit-btn-lg" style="text-decoration: none;">Component Reference</a>
            <a href="code_examples" class="sit-btn sit-btn-secondary sit-btn-lg" style="text-decoration: none;">Code Examples</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>What's Inside?</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <h4 style="color: #FD1875; margin-bottom: 12px;">Modals &amp; Dialogs</h4>
                <p class="sit-text-secondary">Beautiful popup dialogs for confirmations, forms, and complex workflows. Includes alert, confirm, and custom modal types.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <h4 style="color: #FD1875; margin-bottom: 12px;">Toast Notifications</h4>
                <p class="sit-text-secondary">Non-intrusive notification popups for success, error, warning, and info messages. Auto-dismiss with customizable duration.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <h4 style="color: #FD1875; margin-bottom: 12px;">Buttons &amp; Icons</h4>
                <p class="sit-text-secondary">6 button variants, 3 sizes, loading states, and built-in icons. Primary, secondary, outline, ghost, danger, and success styles.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <h4 style="color: #FD1875; margin-bottom: 12px;">Form Controls</h4>
                <p class="sit-text-secondary">Styled inputs, selects, checkboxes, and toggle switches. All with dark theme support and accessibility features.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <h4 style="color: #FD1875; margin-bottom: 12px;">Data Tables</h4>
                <p class="sit-text-secondary">Sortable, filterable, paginated tables for displaying data. Custom column renderers and row click handlers.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="sit-card">
              <div class="sit-card-body">
                <h4 style="color: #FD1875; margin-bottom: 12px;">Progress &amp; Loading</h4>
                <p class="sit-text-secondary">Progress bars (static, striped, animated) and spinners in multiple sizes. Perfect for showing operation status.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Step 1: Include the Toolkit in Your Dashboard</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">To use the toolkit in your own dashboard, add the CSS files to your dashboard's opening tag:</p>

          <div style="background: #1F2527; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 14px; overflow-x: auto;">
            <pre style="margin: 0; color: #A0A0A0;"><code>&lt;dashboard version="1.1" theme="dark"
           <span style="color: #FD1875;">stylesheet="css/sit-core.css,css/sit-components.css"</span>&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>

          <p style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;">If you want to use JavaScript components (modals, toasts, tables), also add the script:</p>

          <div style="background: #1F2527; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 14px; overflow-x: auto;">
            <pre style="margin: 0; color: #A0A0A0;"><code>&lt;dashboard version="1.1" theme="dark"
           <span style="color: #FD1875;">script="sit-toolkit.js"</span>
           stylesheet="css/sit-core.css,css/sit-components.css"&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>

          <div style="margin-top: 20px; padding: 16px; background: rgba(92, 192, 92, 0.1); border-left: 4px solid #5CC05C; border-radius: 4px;">
            <strong style="color: #5CC05C;">Pro Tip:</strong> <span class="sit-text-secondary">Always wrap your HTML content in a <code class="sit-code">&lt;div class="sit-scope"&gt;</code> to ensure styles are applied correctly and don't conflict with Splunk's built-in styles.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

  <row>
    <panel>
      <title>Step 2: Use HTML Panels</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Most toolkit components work inside HTML panels. Here's the basic structure:</p>

          <div style="background: #1F2527; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 14px; overflow-x: auto;">
            <pre style="margin: 0; color: #A0A0A0;"><code>&lt;row&gt;
  &lt;panel&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;My Panel Title&lt;/title&gt;
    &lt;html&gt;
      <span style="color: #FD1875;">&lt;div class="sit-scope"&gt;</span>
        &lt;!-- Your toolkit components go here --&gt;
        &lt;button class="sit-btn sit-btn-primary"&gt;Click Me&lt;/button&gt;
      <span style="color: #FD1875;">&lt;/div&gt;</span>
    &lt;/html&gt;
  &lt;/panel&gt;
&lt;/row&gt;</code></pre>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>

    <panel>
      <title>Step 3: Try It Out!</title>
      <html>
        <div class="sit-scope" style="padding: 20px;">
          <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;">Here's what those buttons look like in action:</p>

          <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-bottom: 20px;">
            <button class="sit-btn sit-btn-primary">Primary</button>
            <button class="sit-btn sit-btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
            <button class="sit-btn sit-btn-outline">Outline</button>
            <button class="sit-btn sit-btn-success">Success</button>
            <button class="sit-btn sit-btn-danger">Danger</button>
          </div>

          <p class="sit-text-secondary" style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Copy this code to create buttons:</p>

          <div style="background: #1F2527; border-radius: 8px; padding: 16px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 13px; overflow-x: auto;">
            <code style="color: #A0A0A0;">&lt;button class="sit-btn sit-btn-primary"&gt;Primary&lt;/button&gt;</code>
          </div>
        </div>
      </html>
    </panel>
  </row>

